# 8C Auto-Qualification Environment Variables
# 
# ⚠️  NOTE: THIS FILE IS NOW OPTIONAL!
# 
# All API tokens (HubSpot, Anthropic, Composio) are automatically loaded from 
# Supabase table `shared_api_tokens` by default. You only need this .env file if:
# 
# 1. You want to OVERRIDE shared tokens with your own keys (for testing/dev)
# 2. You're running GitHub Actions (SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY required there)
# 
# For most users: NO SETUP NEEDED - just run the MCP tool and it will work!
# 
# If you still want to create a .env file, copy this file to .env and fill in values:

# Supabase (required for 8C qualification)
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here  # Only for GitHub Actions

# HubSpot (optional - loaded from Supabase by default)
HUBSPOT_PRIVATE_APP_TOKEN=your-hubspot-token-here

# Anthropic (optional - loaded from Supabase by default)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-api-key-here

# Composio (optional - loaded from Supabase by default)
COMPOSIO_API_KEY=your-composio-api-key-here
COMPOSIO_USER_ID=your-composio-user-id-here

# Where to get these values (if you need to override):
# 
# SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY:
#   Ask admin (Egor) for Supabase credentials
#
# HUBSPOT_PRIVATE_APP_TOKEN:
#   HubSpot → Settings → Integrations → Private Apps → Create token
#   Required scopes: crm.objects.deals.read, crm.objects.deals.write, 
#                    crm.objects.owners.read, crm.schemas.deals.read
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:
#   https://console.anthropic.com/ → API Keys
#
# COMPOSIO_API_KEY / COMPOSIO_USER_ID:
#   Ask admin for Composio credentials (shared account)
